---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Surrey Contracting Limited"
  description="Privacy Policy for Surrey Contracting Limited: how we collect, use, store and protect your personal information in line with UK GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018."
  path="/privacy"
>

<!-- ============ PAGE HERO ============ -->
<section class="page-hero">
  <div class="page-hero-bg" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="page-hero-img" style="background-image:url('/assets/img/bulk-earthworks.jpg')"></div>
    <div class="page-hero-vignette"></div>
  </div>
  <div class="container page-hero-inner">
    <nav class="crumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="12" height="12" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 6l6 6-6 6"/></svg>
      <span>Privacy Policy</span>
    </nav>
    <h1 class="page-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="page-lede">How Surrey Contracting Limited collects, uses, stores and protects your personal information.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ POLICY CONTENT ============ -->
<section class="page-section">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="policy-prose">

      <p class="lede-dark">At Surrey Contracting Limited, we take your privacy very seriously. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, store and protect any personal information you provide to us when you use our website, contact us, request a quote, make an enquiry, or interact with our services.</p>

      <p>Surrey Contracting Limited respects the privacy rights of its website visitors, customers and prospective customers. We recognise the importance of protecting the personal information we collect and will only use your information lawfully, fairly and transparently, in accordance with applicable UK data protection laws, including the UK General Data Protection Regulation and the Data Protection Act 2018.</p>

      <p>By using our website, surreycontracting.co.uk, you acknowledge that your personal information may be processed in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</p>

      <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or how your personal information is used, please contact us at:</p>

      <address>
        Surrey Contracting Limited<br>
        Upper Leewood Farm Yard<br>
        Effingham Common Road<br>
        Leatherhead<br>
        Surrey, KT24 5JQ<br>
        <br>
        Telephone: <a href="tel:01932932650">01932 932650</a><br>
        Email: <a href="mailto:info@surreycontracting.co.uk">info@surreycontracting.co.uk</a>
      </address>

      <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect personal information from you when you:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Submit an enquiry through our website</li>
        <li>Request a quote or consultation</li>
        <li>Contact us by telephone, email or through our website</li>
        <li>Subscribe to marketing communications</li>
        <li>Interact with our website, adverts or online forms</li>
      </ul>
      <p>The information we collect may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name</li>
        <li>Your address</li>
        <li>Your email address</li>
        <li>Your telephone number</li>
        <li>Details about your project or enquiry</li>
        <li>Information you provide in messages or forms</li>
        <li>Technical information, such as your IP address, browser type, device information and website usage data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not intentionally collect unnecessary personal information and only collect the information needed to respond to your enquiry, provide our services, improve our website, and manage our business.</p>

      <h2>How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We may use your personal information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your enquiry</li>
        <li>Provide quotes, consultations or information about our services</li>
        <li>Manage customer relationships</li>
        <li>Process and administer any services you request from us</li>
        <li>Contact you about your enquiry or project</li>
        <li>Improve our website, services and customer experience</li>
        <li>Monitor website performance and visitor behaviour</li>
        <li>Send marketing communications, where you have agreed to receive them</li>
        <li>Measure the effectiveness of our advertising</li>
        <li>Comply with legal, regulatory or business obligations</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

      <h2>Marketing Communications</h2>
      <p>We operate an opt in policy for marketing communications. Where you have chosen to receive marketing from us, we may contact you by email, telephone or other relevant methods.</p>
      <p>You can unsubscribe from marketing communications at any time by contacting us directly or by using any unsubscribe option provided in our communications.</p>

      <h2>Cookies and Similar Technologies</h2>
      <p>Our website is a static site hosted on Netlify. It does not currently use analytics, marketing, advertising or social-media cookies, and does not embed any third-party widgets that place cookies on your device.</p>
      <p>The only third-party request the website makes is to Google Fonts to display the Montserrat typeface; this does not typically place cookies on your device but does share your IP address with Google as part of the font request.</p>
      <p>If we add analytics, advertising or other tools that use cookies in future, we will update this Privacy Policy and our Cookie Policy, and request your consent where required by law. For full details of what is currently used, see our <a href="/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>.</p>

      <h2>Sharing Your Information</h2>
      <p>We may share your personal information with trusted third parties where necessary to operate our business, provide our services, manage enquiries, improve our website, or comply with legal obligations.</p>
      <p>This may include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Website hosting providers</li>
        <li>IT and website support providers</li>
        <li>Email and communication providers</li>
        <li>Analytics and advertising providers, including Google</li>
        <li>Professional advisers, where required</li>
        <li>Other service providers who help us manage enquiries or deliver our services</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Where we share personal information with third party service providers, we only share the information necessary for them to provide their services to us.</p>

      <h2>Website Analytics and Advertising</h2>
      <p>We may use analytics and advertising tools to understand how visitors use our website and to help improve our marketing. These tools may use cookies or similar technologies to collect information about your visit.</p>
      <p>Where legally required, these tools will only be activated after you have given consent through our cookie banner.</p>

      <h2>How Long We Keep Your Information</h2>
      <p>We will only keep your personal information for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, including responding to enquiries, managing customer relationships, maintaining business records, complying with legal obligations, and resolving any disputes.</p>
      <p>When personal information is no longer required, we will delete it securely or anonymise it.</p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under UK data protection law, you have rights in relation to your personal information. These may include the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to the personal information we hold about you</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
        <li>Request deletion of your personal information</li>
        <li>Object to certain types of processing</li>
        <li>Request restriction of processing</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
        <li>Request a copy of your personal information in a portable format</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these rights, please contact us using the details provided in this Privacy Policy.</p>

      <h2>Complaints</h2>
      <p>If you have any questions or complaints about how we use your personal information, please contact us in the first instance using the details above.</p>
      <p>You also have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office, which is the UK supervisory authority for data protection matters.</p>

      <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our business, website, legal obligations or the way we use personal information.</p>
      <p>Any updates will be posted on this page.</p>

      <p class="policy-meta">Last updated: 1 June 2026.</p>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ============ FOOTER ============ -->
</BaseLayout>
